<p class="">My hon. Friend surely overlooks that what they are convicted of by this Tribunal is allowing their minds and judgment to be influenced in the public business by reward and hopes of reward. I understand that Mr. Gibson denies that, I do not know. But I heard the hon. Member for Sowerby (Mr. Belcher) deny it today and it must not be said, therefore, that he admits it.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
